                <h3>Some of <a style="color:#F94D00; text-decoration:none;">my projects.</a></h3>
                    
                <ul class="projects">
                    <li>Spotify Notifications (<a href="https://citruspi.github.io/Spotify-Notifications">Home Page</a> | <a href="http://github.com/citruspi/Spotify-Notifications">GitHub</a>)</li>
            
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>Spotify Notifications bridges Spotify and the OS X Notification Center, providing you with updates when the play state is changed.</p>
                    </blockquote>
            
                    <li>ford.py (<a href="https://github.com/citruspi/ford.py">GitHub</a> | <a href="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/ford.py">Cheeseshop</a>)</li>                
                    
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>ford.py is a static site generator written in Python. It is built on top of the flask package.</p>
                    </blockquote>
            
                    <li>PyUnio (<a href="https://github.com/citruspi/PyUnio">GitHub</a> | <a href="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyunio">Cheeseshop</a>)</li>                
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>PyUnio is a Python implementation of Tezel's Unio. It allows developers to consume API's using predefined definitions.</p>
                    </blockquote>
            
                    <li>Zinc (<a href="https://github.com/citruspi/Zinc">GitHub</a>)</li>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>Zinc is a GUI wrapper for rsync written for OS X. It was originally written to sync iTunes libraries to Android phones.</p>
                    </blockquote>

